b/20150708033525/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/amitabh-launches-new-version-of-mile-sur-mera-tumhara/article1-501675.aspx |archive-date=8 July 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Bolydude Ganeshan\"\n| 2012\n| {{mdash}}\n| [[Ganesh Hegde]]\n| ''Let's Party''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Ganesh-Hegde-makes-Pune-dance/articleshow/11893870.cms |title=Ganesh Hegde makes Pune dance |last=Birajdar |first=Laxmi |date=15 February 2012 |work=The Times of India |access-date=25 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127034051/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Ganesh-Hegde-makes-Pune-dance/articleshow/11893870.cms |archive-date=27 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone]]\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|id=2138653|name=Deepika Padukone}}\n* [http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/index/id/1856 Deepika Padukone] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{featured list}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Padukone, Deepika filmography}}\n[[Category:Indian filmographies]]\n[[Category:Actress filmographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n[[File:Deepika Padukone at Tamasha event.jpg|thumb|alt=A shot of Deepika Padukone|Padukone at an event for ''[[Tamasha (2015 film)|Tamasha]]'' in 2015]]\n[[Deepika Padukone]] is an Indian actress who appears in [[Bollywood|Hindi films]]. Her first screen appearance was in [[Himesh Reshammiya]]'s music video \"Naam Hai Tera\" in 2005.<ref name=\"video\">{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-in-awe-of-beauty-pageant-winners/articleshow/10767352.cms?referral=PM |title=Deepika Padukone in awe of beauty pageant winners |last=Iyer |first=Meena |date=17 November 2011 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=3 August 2013 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180412161455/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-in-awe-of-beauty-pageant-winners/articleshow/10767352.cms?referral=PM |archive-date=12 April 2018}}</ref> Padukone made her film debut by playing the titular role in the [[Kannada]] film  ''[[Aishwarya (film)|Aishwarya]]'' (2006).<ref name=\"debut\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/15aish.htm |title=Deepika's Aishwarya is a must watch |last=Vijayasarathy |first=R.G. |date=15 September 2006 |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055429/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/15aish.htm |archive-date=23 October 2013 |access-date=3 August 2013}}</ref> Her first Hindi film release came the following year with [[Farah Khan]]'s melodrama ''[[Om Shanti Om]]'', in which she played dual roles opposite [[Shah Rukh Khan]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54373 |title=Movie Review: Om Shanti Om |last=Adarsh |first=Taran |date=7 November 2007 |work=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |access-date=18 December 2007 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBYXxYy?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54373 |archive-date=27 September 2013}}</ref> For her performance, she won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]] and also received a [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] nomination. Her sole film role in 2008 was as one of [[Ranbir Kapoor]]'s love interests in ''[[Bachna Ae Haseeno]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?238292 |title=Movie Review: Bachna Ae Haseeno |last=Joshi |first=Namrata |date=1 September 2008 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |access-date=19 July 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927152352/http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?238292 |archive-date=27 September 2013}}</ref>\n\nPadukone's first film release of 2009, the [[Kung fu film|kung fu]] comedy  ''[[Chandni Chowk to China]]'' opposite [[Akshay Kumar]], proved to be a box office flop.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=348&catName=TGlmZXRpbWUgV29ybGR3aWRlIEluIFVTICQ= |title=Top Lifetime Grossers Worldwide (US $) |website=[[Box Office India]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602093609/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU%3D |archive-date=2 June 2013 |access-date=11 November 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-01-20/news/27650181_1_domestic-box-office-bollywood-film-kinng |title=Chandni Chowk to China crosses Rs 33 cr at local box office |last=Sharma |first=Amit |date=20 January 2009 |work=[[The Economic Times]] |access-date=6 August 2013 |last2=Verma Ambwani |first2=Meenakshi |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305091941/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-01-20/news/27650181_1_domestic-box-office-bollywood-film-kinng |archive-date=5 March 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, her next release, [[Imtiaz Ali (director)|Imtiaz Ali]]'s romance ''[[Love Aaj Kal]]'' grossed {{INRConvert|1.2|b}} worldwide,<ref name=\"top\">{{Cite web |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3997&nCat= |title=Top All Time Worldwide Grossers Updated |date=11 May 2012 |website=Box Office India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105215110/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4409&nCat= |archive-date=5 November 2013 |access-date=13 October 2013}}</ref> and garnered her a second Best Actress nomination at Filmfare.<ref name=\"ff09\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/725/ |title=Nominations for 55th Idea Filmfare Awards 2009 |date=11 February 2010 |work=Bollywood Hungama |access-date=27 April 2011 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020180943/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/725/ |archive-date=20 October 2014}}</ref> Padukone had five film releases in 2010. The comedy ''[[Housefull (2010 film)|Housefull]]'' was a commercial success,<ref name=\"top\" /> though her other four releases failed at the box office.<ref name=\"bo2010\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=318&catName=MjAxMA== |title=Box Office 2010 |publisher=Box office India |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014062657/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=318&catName=MjAxMA%3D%3D |archive-date=14 October 2013 |access-date=14 May 2012}}</ref> The series of poorly received films continued with both her 2011 releases{{mdash}}the drama ''[[Aarakshan]]'' and the comedy ''[[Desi Boyz]]''.<ref name=\"making\">{{Cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-17/news-interviews/40009313_1_deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-deepika-imtiaz-ali |title=The making of Deepika Padukone |last=Pal |first=Chandrima |date=17 June 2013 |work=The Times of India |access-date=27 July 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627020227/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-17/news-interviews/40009313_1_deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-deepika-imtiaz-ali |archive-date=27 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> The acclaimed role of an impulsive party-girl in [[Homi Adajania]]'s ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]'' (2012) proved to be a breakthrough for Padukone and she received several acting nominations for it.<ref name=\"making\" /><ref name=\"awards\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/1856 |title=Deepika Padukone&nbsp;\u2014 Awards |work=Bollywood Hungama |access-date=5 September 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCqDjGs?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/1856 |archive-date=27 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/cocktail-deepika-padukone-daina-penty-saif-ali-khan/1/207582.html |title=Was conscious about my look in Cocktail: Deepika |work=[[India Today]] |date=11 July 2012 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCBnq5n?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/cocktail-deepika-padukone-daina-penty-saif-ali-khan/1/207582.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead }}<br />{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-verdict-cocktail-works-but-in-bits/story-cFNQiVGyPXFUTKmsSUSBEN.html |title=Critics verdict: Cocktail works, but in bits |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=13 July 2012 |accessdate=7 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304122353/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-verdict-cocktail-works-but-in-bits/story-cFNQiVGyPXFUTKmsSUSBEN.html |archivedate= 4 March 2016 }}</ref>\n\nPadukone found further success in 2013 when all four of her films were box office hits.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-lucky-fourth-time-with-ramleela/1196368/ |title=Deepika Padukone lucky fourth time with 'Ram-Leela' |last=Goyal |first=Divya |date=18 November 2013 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=4 December 2013 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152120/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-lucky-fourth-time-with-ramleela/1196368/ |archive-date=22 February 2014}}</ref> Among these were two of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]]{{mdash}}the romantic comedies ''[[Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani]]'' and ''[[Chennai Express]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6355&nCat |title=Dhoom 3 All Time Number One Worldwide Grosser: 500 cr Plus Expected |website=Box Office India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102192306/http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6355&nCat |archive-date=2 January 2014 |access-date=3 January 2014}}</ref> She also won the Filmfare Award for Best Actress for playing a character based on [[Juliet]] in [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]'s tragic romance ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'' (2013).<ref name=\"ff13\">{{Cite web |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-2014-deepika-padukone-wins-best-actress-award-farhan-akhtar-best-actor/447639-8-66.html |title=Filmfare Awards 2014: Deepika Padukone wins Best Actress award, Farhan Akhtar Best Actor |date=25 January 2014 |publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125110704/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-2014-deepika-padukone-wins-best-actress-award-farhan-akhtar-best-actor/447639-8-66.html |archive-date=25 January 2014 |access-date=25 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-party-girl-deepika-padukone-gets-serious-1819664 |title=Party girl Deepika Padukone gets serious |last=KBR |first=Upala |date=7 April 2013 |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |access-date=24 June 2015 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141014003716/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-party-girl-deepika-padukone-gets-serious-1819664 |archive-date=14 October 2014}}</ref> In 2014, Padukone appeared in the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] animation film ''[[Kochadaiiyaan]]'' and played a bar dancer in the top-grossing heist film ''[[Happy New Year (2014 film)|Happy New Year]]''.<ref name=\"kocha\">{{Cite web |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/regional/deepika-padukone-working-in-kochadaiiyaan-was-an-experience-637867 |title=Deepika Padukone: Working in Kochadaiiyaan was an experience |date=10 March 2014 |publisher=[[NDTV]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627013948/http://movies.ndtv.com/regional/deepika-padukone-working-in-kochadaiiyaan-was-an-experience-637867 |archive-date=27 June 2015 |access-date=23 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/happy-new-year-review-if-indulgences-were-trimmed-this-might-have-been-a-more-enjoyable-film/508330-8-66.html |title='Happy New Year' review |last=Masand |first=Rajeev |date=25 October 2014 |publisher=CNN-IBN |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141111041401/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/happy-new-year-review-if-indulgences-were-trimmed-this-might-have-been-a-more-enjoyable-film/508330-8-66.html |archive-date=11 November 2014 |access-date=9 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/Collections/world_total#.VbC_lvmSiYA |title=Top Worldwide Grossers All Time |website=Box Office India |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150919181138/http://boxofficeindia.com/Collections/world_total |archive-date=19 September 2015 |access-date=23 July 2015}}</ref> The following year, she played a headstrong architect in [[Shoojit Sircar]]'s acclaimed comedy-drama ''[[Piku]]'', which earned Padukone her second Best Actress award at Filmfare, and portrayed the warrior [[Mastani]] in Bhansali's highly successful historical romance ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]''.<ref name=\"Chatterjee\">{{Cite web |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/piku-movie-review-1124 |title=Piku Movie Review |last=Chatterjee |first=Saibal |date=8 May 2015 |publisher=NDTV |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150510190128/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/piku-movie-review-1124 |archive-date=10 May 2015 |access-date=10 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/piku-review-roundup-simple-classy-charming-film-631700 |title='Piku' Review Roundup: A Film that's all Heart |last=Mehta |first=Ankita |date=7 May 2015 |work=[[International Business Times]] |access-date=25 January 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509200624/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/piku-review-roundup-simple-classy-charming-film-631700 |archive-date=9 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Filmfare2016\">{{cite news|title=Full list of winners of the 61st Britannia Filmfare Awards |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |work=[[Filmfare]] |date=15 January 2016 |accessdate=16 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316165017/http://www.filmfare.com/news/full-list-of-winners-of-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11841.html |archivedate=16 March 2016 }}<br />{{cite web|last=Sharma |first=Dhriti |title='Bajirao Mastani' Box Office collection: Ranveer-Deepika-Priyanka's love triangle sees massive growth, mints Rs 181.01 cr |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/bajirao-mastani-box-office-collection-ranveer-deepika-priyankas-love-triangle-sees-massive-growth-mints-rs-181-01-cr_1846158.html |publisher=[[Zee News]] |date=17 January 2016 |accessdate=25 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120105904/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/bajirao-mastani-box-office-collection-ranveer-deepika-priyankas-love-triangle-sees-massive-growth-mints-rs-181-01-cr_1846158.html |archivedate=20 January 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"bm\">{{Cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-ranveers-bajirao-mastani-box-office-collections-unstoppable-earns-rs-162-35-cr/ |title=Deepika, Ranveer\u2019s \u2018Bajirao Mastani\u2019 box office collections unstoppable, earns Rs.177.35 cr. |date=11 January 2016 |work=The Indian Express |access-date=25 January 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125051712/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-ranveers-bajirao-mastani-box-office-collections-unstoppable-earns-rs-162-35-cr/ |archive-date=25 January 2016}}</ref> Padukone's first project in [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]]{{mdash}}the action film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage|x